title: Seychelles Core Inflation Rate
description: Core consumer prices in Seychelles increased 0.95 percent in October of 2022 over the same month in the previous year. Core Inflation Rate in Seychelles averaged 2.94 percent from 2016 until 2022, reaching an all time high of 10.70 percent in May of 2021 and a record low of -0.59 percent in June of 2016. This page provides - Seychelles Core Inflation Rate- actual values, historical data, forecast, chart, statistics, economic calendar and news.
author: National Bureau of Statistics, Seychelles
